==English==

===Intransitive verb===
'''[[stand]] [[up]]'''

# To [[rise]] from a lying or sitting position.
#: '''''Stand up''', then sit down again.''
# To [[withstand]]; to [[survive]] to resist [[abuse]] or [[conditions]].
#:''The paint looks good, but I don't know if it will '''stand up''' to years of weather.''
#{{cricket}} (''of a wicket-keeper'') to stand immediately behind the wicket so as to catch balls from a [[slow bowler|slow]] or [[spin bowler]], and to attempt to [[stump]] the batsman

